Just watch an interview with Frank Schaeffer, co author of AWOL: The
Unexcused Absence of America's Upper Classes from Military Service --
and How It Hurts Our Country. During the interview on CSPAN Schaeffer
said the draft was initially instituted in 1917 because too many
children of the rich were volunteering for service. IIRC this
parallels the British experience in the same war. Now the number of
Ivy leaguers in the military is less than 1%, and I would personally
bet the "safe" services, Air Force and Navy, have a large share of
that number.

WI the Vietnam War was as much a crusade as WWI and WWII? Where it was
considered a duty to serve your country rather than a sign of
stupidity?

Is there any POD that would make such dedication normal rather than a
sign of stupidity? Is there a way to get an Army that represents all
of the classes in America or are we letting the "volunteer" nature
serve as an excuse for our children avoiding service?
</POST>
