A large proportion of military personnel are too
young to be Ivy league graduates.

The Ivies graduate about 12,000 people a year,
not counting foreign students.

That's less than 1% of the ~4M Americans who
turn 21 each year, so it should be no surprise
at all that less than 1% of Americans in the
military are Ivy league graduates.

&lt;1% of Ivy league graduates are serving military personnel?

Could be.

Brown, Harvard, and Columbia don't even have ROTC programs.

But there are ~1.4M people in the services, and there
are 105M Americas age 20-44. Only about 1.4% of eligible
Americans are in the services.

