Yes, and I would personally bet that the sun
will rise in the east tomorrow.

As of 6/30/2005, the Air Force and Navy had 717,000
personnel; the Army and Marine Corps had 673,000.

It is overwhelmingly likely that "a large share"
of any category of military personnel would be
in two services that are a majority of military
personnel.

However, if the question is where the scions of
wealthy families are to be found, the answer is:
primarily in combat arms. Working-class and under-
class youths may join the services for college money
and job skills. Upper-class youth don't have that
need. Anything the service could provide they already
have or can get elsewhere.

If they join up, it is to shoot big guns, jump
out of planes, drive tanks, fly jets, blow
things up, learn to kill with bare hands: to be
_warriors_.
